    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Dynamic Array Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    max-width: 700px;\n    margin: 2em auto;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n    color: #333;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n  .container {\n    background: white;\n    padding: 1em 2em 2em 2em;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n  }\n  label {\n    display: block;\n    margin-top: 1em;\n  }\n  input[type=\"number\"] {\n    width: 60px;\n    padding: 0.2em;\n    margin-left: 0.5em;\n  }\n  button {\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    padding: 0.5em 1em;\n    font-size: 1em;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    border: 1px solid #007bff;\n    background-color: #007bff;\n    color: white;\n    transition: background-color 0.3s ease;\n  }\n  button:hover {\n    background-color: #0056b3;\n  }\n  #output {\n    margin-top: 1.5em;\n    padding: 1em;\n    background: #e1ecf4;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    min-height: 3em;\n    font-family: monospace;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    word-wrap: break-word;\n  }\n  .explanation {\n    background: #d1e7dd;\n    padding: 1em;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    margin-top: 1.5em;\n    font-size: 0.95em;\n    color: #0f5132;\n    border: 1px solid #badbcc;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>Dynamic Array Demonstration</h1>\n    <p>This demo simulates a dynamic array (like C++ <code>std::vector</code>) by managing a fixed-size underlying array and resizing (re-allocating) automatically as elements are added beyond its capacity.</p>\n\n    <label for=\"elementInput\">Enter a number to add:</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"elementInput\" />\n    <button id=\"addBtn\">Add to Dynamic Array</button>\n    <button id=\"clearBtn\" style=\"background-color:#dc3545; border-color:#dc3545;\">Clear Array</button>\n\n    <div id=\"output\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"true\"></div>\n\n    <div class=\"explanation\">\n      <strong>How this Dynamic Array works:</strong><br>\n      - Starts with a small fixed capacity.<br>\n      - When you add elements, if the current capacity is exceeded, it \"resizes\" by creating a new internal array (double the capacity), copying existing elements over, and then adding the new element.<br>\n      - This mimics underlying logic in many dynamic array implementations where capacity grows exponentially to keep amortized insertion efficient.<br>\n      - You can see the internal capacity and size updates as you add elements.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n<script>\n  class DynamicArray {\n    constructor() {\n      this.size = 0; // Number of elements stored\n      this.capacity = 2; // Initial capacity\n      this.array = new Array(this.capacity); // Internal fixed-size storage\n    }\n\n    // Add an element, resizing if needed\n    push(element) {\n      if (this.size === this.capacity) {\n        this._resize();\n      }\n      this.array[this.size] = element;\n      this.size++;\n    }\n\n    // Resize internal array to double capacity\n    _resize() {\n      this.capacity *= 2;\n      const newArray = new Array(this.capacity);\n      for (let i = 0; i < this.size; i++) {\n        newArray[i] = this.array[i];\n      }\n      this.array = newArray;\n    }\n\n    // Get current elements as array\n    toArray() {\n      return this.array.slice(0, this.size);\n    }\n\n    // Clear the dynamic array completely\n    clear() {\n      this.size = 0;\n      this.capacity = 2;\n      this.array = new Array(this.capacity);\n    }\n  }\n\n  (() => {\n    const dynArray = new DynamicArray();\n    const elementInput = document.getElementById('elementInput');\n    const addBtn = document.getElementById('addBtn');\n    const clearBtn = document.getElementById('clearBtn');\n    const output = document.getElementById('output');\n\n    function updateOutput() {\n      output.textContent =\n`Dynamic Array Contents: [ ${dynArray.toArray().join(', ')} ]\nSize: ${dynArray.size}\nCapacity: ${dynArray.capacity}`;\n    }\n\n    addBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const valStr = elementInput.value.trim();\n      if (valStr === '') {\n        alert('Please enter a number to add.');\n        return;\n      }\n      const val = Number(valStr);\n      if (isNaN(val)) {\n        alert('Invalid number.');\n        return;\n      }\n      dynArray.push(val);\n      updateOutput();\n      elementInput.value = '';\n      elementInput.focus();\n    });\n\n    clearBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      dynArray.clear();\n      updateOutput();\n      elementInput.value = '';\n      elementInput.focus();\n    });\n\n    // Initial output\n    updateOutput();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
